The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has held the Tamil Nadu government responsible for the stampede at a flood relief camp in Chennai in December.

 The incident occurred because of the negligence of your officers, the court said. 

 The observations came during the hearing of a petition filed by the Jayalalithaa government seeking cancellation of the bail granted to DMK councillor K. Dhanasekaran, one of the accused in the stampede case.

 Toronto (PTI): The Bata shoe museum here has announced a reward of US$ 25,000 for the safe return of a pair of slippers worn by the Nizam of Hyderabad in the 1790s and two other artefacts stolen from its premises on Sunday. The slippers, valued at US $140,000, are embroidered with gold and encrusted with diamonds and rubies.

 New Delhi (PTI): The guards at Prime Minister Manmohan Singhs residence detained a man carrying kerosene and a lighter on Friday. The man from Nagpur, in his late twenties, said he was unable to bear the life as an unemployed and was about to immolate himself.

 Chennai (PTI): A bill which spares students coming out of schools under the Tamil Nadu board from taking entrance examinations for admission to professional courses was passed by the Assembly on Friday.




